Nobody=E2=80=99s Perfect

So=E2=80=A6 do we believe the Tyson-Paul numbers? Skeptics have pointed to =
Nielsen=E2=80=99s Streaming Platform Ratings from that night. Per that repo=
rt, all of Netflix averaged 25 million U.S. viewers on a per-minute basis l=
ast Friday in the 8 p.m. ET to 1 a.m. ET window. It=E2=80=99s impossible to=
 discern from the report how many of those 25 million people watched the bo=
xing matches. (By comparison, in that same window the previous Friday, Netf=
lix averaged 11 million viewers across its entire service.) During the Tayl=
or-Serrano fight, the SPR report registered 25 million U.S. Netflix viewers=
=2E Its peak viewership during that win=
dow was 28.2 million viewers in the U.=
S.

Obviously, it=E2=80=99s hard to square those numbers with those released by=
 Netflix. =E2=80=9CWhen they came out with such a big number, the whole ind=
ustry attacked them and, I think, they looked
kind of ridiculous,=E2=80=9D one traditional media exec said. =E2=80=9CIf t=
hey had come out with a number around 25 million, that still would have bee=
n a huge win for them to claim.=E2=80=9D

Netflix isn=E2=80=99t commenting beyond the releases it already put out. Bu=
t it=E2=80=99s not alone in wanting to change the way the business counts s=
treaming viewers. Last winter, using Nielsen, Peacock reported 23 million v=
iewers, which stands as the most streamed NFL game to date. But NBC sources=
 said internal data showed a higher number of viewers, which is a frequent =
complaint among streamers. Amazon, for example, consistently says that Niel=
sen underreports its NFL streaming numbers, too. Alas, one hallmark of this=
 new era is that everyone complains about Nielsen. Let=E2=80=99s see what h=
appens, though, if the NFL Christmas games can=E2=80=99t outrate a women=E2=
=80=99s boxing match.

From the Cheap Seats

On ESPN=E2=80=99s =E2=80=98Inside the NBA=E2=80=99 deal: =E2=80=9CI have se=
en reports that ESPN is not exchanging cash for the Inside the NBA/Big 12 f=
ootball and basketball trade. But that is not saying they are not exchangin=
g value. I am pretty sure that Turner is not losing money on what they pay =
the talent and production for Inside, so they should get equal value. If ES=
PN is trying to say that there is no real value in the games they are excha=
nging, then that brings into question whether the network overpaid for the =
Big 12 package. If ESPN is so focused on live sports, why did it just give =
up more live sports?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A former media analyst

On ESPN dealing with Sir Charles=E2=80=99 comments: =E2=80=9CHistorically, =
this would be a prelude to disaster in Bristol. How well do we think it wil=
l go over these days in central
Connecticut when Charles gets agitated about something with ESPN and candid=
ly speaks his mind?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A league executive

On Dr. John Malone: =E2=80=9CComcast is spinning off linear networks. Chart=
er will acquire Liberty Broadband. And Dr. John supports merging Charter wi=
th Comcast. If anyone thought Malone was slowing down and heading for the s=
unset phase of his career, they would be wrong. Dead wrong.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=94A cable guy

